<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="5" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:18.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Form&nbsp;6-K</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:12.0pt;font-weight:bold;">REPORT OF
FOREIGN PRIVATE ISSUER PURSUANT TO RULE 13a-16 OR 15d-16 UNDER THE<br>
SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">For the month of September, 2010.</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Commission File Number</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="5" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:18.0pt;font-weight:bold;">AGNICO-EAGLE
MINES LIMITED</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Translation
of registrant&#146;s name into English)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">145
King Street East, Suite&nbsp;400, Toronto, Ontario M5C 2Y7</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(Address
of principal executive office)</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Indicate by check mark whether the registrant files
or will file annual reports under cover of Form&nbsp;20-F or Form&nbsp;40-F.<br>
Form&nbsp;20-F&nbsp;</font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">x</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;Form&nbsp;40-F&nbsp;</font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">o</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Indicate by check mark if
the registrant is submitting the Form&nbsp;6-K in paper as permitted by
Regulation S-T Rule&nbsp;101 (b)( 1): </font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">o</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Note: </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Regulation S-T Rule&nbsp;101 (b)( 1) only permits the submission in
paper of a Form&nbsp;6-K if submitted solely to provide an attached annual
report to security holders.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Indicate by check mark if
the registrant is submitting the Form&nbsp;6-K in paper as permitted by
Regulation S-T Rule&nbsp;101 (b)(7): </font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">o</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Note: </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Regulation S-T Rule&nbsp;101(b)(7)&nbsp;only permits the submission in
paper of a Form&nbsp;6-K if submitted to furnish a report or other document
that the registrant foreign private issuer must furnish and make public under
the laws of the jurisdiction in which the registrant is incorporated, domiciled
or legally organized (the registrant&#146;s &#147;home country&#148;), or under the rules&nbsp;of
the home country exchange on which the registrant&#146;s securities are traded, as
long as the report or other document is not a press release, is not required to
be and has not been distributed to the registrant&#146;s security holders, and, if
discussing a material event, has already been the subject of a Form&nbsp;6-K
submission or other Commission filing on EDGAR.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Indicate by check mark whether the registrant by
furnishing the information contained in this Form&nbsp;is also thereby
furnishing the information to the Commission pursuant to Rule&nbsp;12g3-2(b)&nbsp;under
the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. Yes&nbsp;</font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">o</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;No&nbsp;</font><font size="2" face="Wingdings" style="font-size:10.0pt;">x</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">If &#147;Yes&#148; is marked,
indicate below the file number assigned to the registrant in connection with Rule&nbsp;12g3-2(b):
82-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(All amounts expressed in U.S. dollars unless otherwise noted)</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">AGNICO-EAGLE PROVIDES EXPLORATION
UPDATE ON 2010 ACTIVITIES:</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">MINERALIZATION EXTENDED AT DEPTH
AT KITTILA;</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">NEW ZONE FOUND AT PINOS
ALTOS;</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">AGGRESSIVE PROGRAM UNDERWAY
AT MELIADINE</font></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Toronto (September&nbsp;8, 2010) - <b>Agnico-Eagle Mines Limited</b> (&#147;Agnico-Eagle&#148;
or the &#147;Company&#148;) is pleased to provide an update on its 2010 exploration
program.&#160; During the course of 2010, the
Company&#146;s programs have resulted in expansions of several mineralized zones at
the Company&#146;s operations, most significantly at Kittila and Pinos Altos.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Additionally, due to the acquisition
of the Meliadine property on July&nbsp;6, 2010 and the acceleration of
exploration at other properties, and the positive results overall, the company&#146;s
exploration budget for 2010 has been increased by more than 45% to $110
million.&#160; This is double of what was
spent in 2009, with $25 million having been spent to the end of July.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Highlights of the 2010 exploration program to
date include:</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 45.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At Kittila:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Deep
mineralization at the Suuri and Roura zones has been extended northward,
increasing the strike length by approximately 30% at 900 metres below
surface.&#160; Deposit remains open on strike
and at depth</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Hole
ROU-09-002, containing one of the thickest drill intersections to date on the
property, indicates the potential for underground mining in a previously
untested area</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Rimpi
zone mineralization deepened by 100 metres to almost 700 metres below surface
as gold continues to be encountered along strike to the north</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 45.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At Pinos Altos:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Cubiro
vein continues to yield quality gold intercepts. Mineralization now extends to
230 metres below surface.&#160; May&nbsp;result
in a stand-alone mining operation.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Step-out
drilling discovered the new Cubiro West vein zone approximately 200 metres away</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 45.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At Meliadine:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">$130-million
budget approved, including 200-kilometre drill program, bulk sample, permitting
and proposed all-season road construction over next 2.5 years</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">High
grade drill results continue to suggest growth and conversion potential of the
five million ounce resource over the next several years</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Early
drilling results suggest possible combination of open pit and underground
scenarios at F zone</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Symbol" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#183;</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Feasibility
study expected to be completed in 2013.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 81.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;With six operating mines driving
record operating and financial results, the focus for Agnico-Eagle turns to
continued production growth through optimization and expansion of these
mines.&#160; At the same time, we have begun
an aggressive exploration program at all of our new mines and our newly
acquired Meliadine project, as we feel the exploration potential is excellent
and these deposits are still relatively under-explored&#148; said Sean Boyd,
Vice-Chairman and CEO. &#147;Recent exploration results, particularly at Kittila,
Pinos Altos, Goldex and Meliadine, have confirmed our understanding of the
potential to continue to grow our reserve and resource base through
exploration.&#160; With the largest drilling
program in our history now underway, we look forward to getting a better
understanding of the ultimate size of our deposits and incorporating these
results into our ongoing expansion studies&#148; added Mr.&nbsp;Boyd.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Kittila &#151; Mineralization Continues to Be
Discovered at Depth and to the North</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
overall reserve and resource envelopes of the Kittila property have grown
consistently since Agnico-Eagle acquired the property in 2005, transforming it
into the largest gold deposit in Scandinavia.&#160;
The current mineralized zones remain wide open for further expansion and
warrant further exploration along strike and at depth.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Prompted by the large increase in Kittila
reserves and resources at the end of 2009, Agnico-Eagle is actively studying
the possibility of increasing the capacity of the mine above its 3,000 tonne
per day design rate.&#160; The main exploration
objectives in 2010 are to drill the Suuri North and Central Roura zones to
convert and expand the gold resources between 600 and 1,100 metres below
surface.&#160; The 2010 drill results will be
incorporated in a feasibility study which is currently investigating scenarios
for increasing the mining rate and plant throughput.&#160; The study is now scheduled for completion in
the second half of 2011.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Including shallower exploration drilling in the
Rimpi, Ketola and Etela zones, and conversion drilling at Suuri South, overall
drilling through the end of July&nbsp;has totalled 58,570 metres out of
approximately 80,000 metres expected for the full year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Roura
Exploration Drilling Returns One of Thickest Gold Intersections to Date</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Drilling
is ongoing below the Roura zones.&#160; This
drilling is largely intended to convert resource to reserve, but also to extend
the resource envelope to the north from its current limit at 650 metres down to
a depth of 1,100 metres or more.&#160;
Selected holes and intersections are presented in the following tables
and linked sections.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Selected
Roura Drill Results</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="93%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:93.34%;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2<a name="PB_2_004804_5335"></a></font></p>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='2',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Hole
ROU-09-002 has returned one of the most significant intersections at depth, to
date, on the property with 6.00 grams per tonne (g/t) over an estimated true
width of 30.0 metres.&#160; This intersection
is approximately 920 metres below surface and approximately 300 metres north of
the current resource envelope.&#160; This
represents an increase of the known strike length at this depth by
approximately </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">30% to the north.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Kittila
Mine Longitudinal Section</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i002.jpg"></font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3<a name="PB_3_004804_5796"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='3',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Kittila
Mine Longitudinal Section&nbsp;Inset</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i003.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Additionally, at 850 metres depth and
approximately 40 metres to the west, the same hole yielded another intercept of
5.92 g/t gold over 4.0 metres.&#160; This wide
two-part intersection is similar to previous results on the property where
significant zones of gold mineralization are marked by wide zones comprised of
multiple parallel lenses.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There were also other significant gold-bearing
intercepts outside of the current resource envelope.&#160; Hole ROU-09-001D intersected gold mineralization
at almost 600 metres depth in an area previously thought to be barren.&#160; Holes ROU-10010B and 014 have pushed the
known extent of the deep mineralization in the Roura area northward more than
100 metres towards the previously mentioned Rou-09-002 drill intersections.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Through the remainder of 2010 and into 2011,
this important 500 metre by 500 metre target area will continue to be
tested.&#160; For reference, the adjacent
roughly 500 metre by 500 metre area to the south contained (in the 2009
year-end estimate) 0.9 million ounces of probable reserves (5.8 million tonnes
at 5.0 g/t gold), 0.3 million ounces of indicated resource (4.2 million tonnes
at 2.3 g/t gold) and 0.4 million ounces of inferred resources (2.9 million
tonnes at 3.9 g/t gold).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A budget supplement of $4.5 million has been
approved to confirm the continuity of mineralization around the hole ROU-09-002
intercepts between 600 and 1,100 metres depth.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Deep Exploration Program Underway</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">At the end of June, a deep exploration drill
program began below the 1,300-metre depth in the Suuri and Roura zones.&#160; The purpose of this program is to test the
favourable Kittila mine horizon on a wide spacing below the current level of
exploration in order to assess an exploration shaft option in the expansion
study described previously.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">While the first drill hole of the program,
ROU-10-029, is still in progress, preliminary results are positive, with
typical, albeit narrow intervals of arsenopyrite mineralization (generally </font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4<a name="PB_4_004804_2897"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">associated with gold) evident between 1,310
metres and 1,320 metres below surface.&#160;
Assays are pending.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Beginning in early to mid-2011, the Company
expects to be able to perform exploration drilling from the underground ramp
for the first time.&#160; This is expected to
facilitate deeper drilling and also to speed up the exploration program as the
holes will be significantly shorter.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Suuri Infill and Resource Conversion Drilling
Continues to be Successful</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Conversion drilling in sectors of indicated and
inferred resource within the current Suuri North zone was also successful below
600 metres depth.&#160; Drill hole SUU-10-001
intersected 6.25 g/t gold over 17.3 metres at the edge of the current reserves
in a sector where the average thickness is about 4.5 metres.&#160; Another positive result in the Suuri area was
a 10.6 metre intersection grading 9.91 g/t gold (hole SUU-09-004D), which
extends a lens comprising the deep Suuri zone at least 30 metres to the north,
at approximately 800 metres depth.&#160; This
is an area where there were no resources previously reported.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Conversion and infill drilling will continue
during 2010 in the Suuri zones.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Selected
Rimpi Drill Results</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
Rimpi zone is the most northerly zone, to date, within the Kittila mining lease
area.&#160; While it currently only contains
approximately 5% of the gold reserves, it is a growing zone that has only recently
become a focus.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Geophysics
and follow-up exploration drilling has suggested significant resource potential
at relatively shallow depths beneath the currently known resource and reserve
envelope and also downplunge to the north (below previous shallow drilling that
indicated the zone was cut-off).</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">These two drill holes intercepted gold
mineralization below the current Rimpi resource envelope along strike to the
north of the main Suuri and Roura zones.&#160;
These holes were drilled to test geophysical anomalies downplunge of
Rimpi which were found in 2009.&#160; These
holes intercepted mineralized lenses almost 700 metres below surface, strongly </font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5<a name="PB_5_004804_3020"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">indicating that Rimpi extends at least another
100 metres northward and further at depth.&#160;
This would be consistent with the plunge and trend of the adjacent Suuri
and Roura zones.&#160; Preparations are
underway to pursue exploration in this area, near the northern limit of the
Kittila mining lease, in the upcoming winter drilling season.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Pinos
Altos &#151; New Parallel Zone Extends Cubiro Deposit to West</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A $10.8-million exploration program
is planned for 2010 on the 11,000 hectare Pinos Altos property in Chihuahua
State, Mexico.&#160; This program is divided
between converting and extending resources in the areas of the Santo Nino and
Oberon de Weber mines and the Creston Mascota satellite mine development, and
also exploring several potential new satellite operations such as the Sinter
deposit and the new Cubiro zones, which already have initial gold resources.&#160; The existence of multiple satellite zones on
the overall Pinos Altos property continues to confirm the significant
exploration potential that originally attracted Agnico-Eagle to this area.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Main Cubiro Zone Continues to Fill-In</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In the regional exploration program,
the Cubiro area at the northwest end of the Pinos Altos property has shown the
most exciting exploration results, to date, in 2010.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Pinos Altos Property Geology Map</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i004.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Company has completed 34 drill
holes (11,952 metres) at Cubiro in 2010, following up 49 drill holes (11,856
metres) in 2009.&#160; Significant recent
results from this area are shown in the table below.&#160; The drill hole pierce points can be seen on the
composite longitudinal section for the Cubiro and Cubiro West vein zones.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">These
assay results are preliminary, pending routine check analyses</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Intersections from new drill holes
such as CB-09-049 and -052 have confirmed that the grade is consistent in the
main Cubiro gold-silver vein zone and that the thicknesses may allow for a bulk
mining situation.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7<a name="PB_7_004804_141"></a></font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">New Gold Discovery at Cubiro West</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The newly discovered Cubiro West
vein zone is roughly parallel to the Cubiro vein, but is located approximately
200 metres to the southwest.&#160; This new
zone dips steeply to the southwest, while the original Cubiro vein discovery
dips steeply to the northeast.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Cubiro West Cross Section&nbsp;25</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i006.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This new zone was discovered during
step-out drilling from the main vein.&#160;
The best results to date are from drill hole CB-10-082 that intersected
an estimated true thickness of 10.3 metres grading 4.26 g/t gold, and
CB-10-079, which yielded 18.2 metres grading 3.47 g/t gold closely followed by
7.7 metres grading 2.36 g/t gold.&#160;
Drilling is underway with one portable rig, and a second drill rig will
soon be added to determine the extensions of the mineralization.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="16%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:16.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Cubiro
  West vein</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="12%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:12.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">exploration</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="9%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:9.0%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">320.5</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>

</table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><i><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-style:italic;">These
assay results are preliminary, pending routine check analyses.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">It is anticipated that Cubiro and
Cubiro West could eventually be mined as a satellite deposit of Pinos
Altos.&#160; A study contemplating the mining
method and processing preference is expected to begin in 2011.&#160; These discoveries also suggest the
possibility of finding other en-echelon vein zones in this region.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">8<a name="PB_8_123943_7056"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='8',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Meliadine &#151; Major Program Preparing for
Feasibility Work</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On July&nbsp;6, 2010, Agnico-Eagle acquired the
Meliadine advanced gold project, located approximately 25 kilometres from
Rankin Inlet in Nunavut, Canada.&#160; Details
of the acquisition and the Meliadine mineral resources are contained in Company
news releases dated July&nbsp;6 and July&nbsp;28, 2010.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The goal of the current exploration program is
to bring the project through to the completion of a feasibility study in
2013.&#160; A $130 million budget over the
next two and a half years was approved in July&nbsp;2010, including 200
kilometres of exploration and infill drilling, an underground bulk sample,
construction of a permanent road and a permanent, all-season camp.&#160; The six-month road construction period will
begin when permits are received, which is expected in the second half of 2011.&#160; The Company expects to proceed with permitting,
while completing the feasibility study.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Meliadine Project Geology Map</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i007.jpg"></font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">9<a name="PB_9_004804_8146"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='9',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The $26 million budget for the remainder of
2010 involves approximately 25,000 metres of drilling, as well as mobilizing
equipment for the extension of two underground sublevels which represent the
bulk sample program.&#160; A new trailer camp
that is able to accommodate 100 people has been purchased for Meliadine and is
expected to arrive in Rankin Inlet during the next few months.&#160; Diamond drilling this year began in March,
and through the end of July&nbsp;totalled approximately 20,000 metres.&#160; The drilling program included 47 geotechnical
drill holes and 44 conversion drill holes at each of Tiriganiaq and F zone.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">High Grade Tiriganiaq Zone Continues to Grow</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The main Tiriganiaq zone at Meliadine contains
a series of sub-parallel gold zones.&#160; The
deposit is characterized by the occurrence of coarse visible gold and numerous
anomalously high gold grades being returned in diamond drilling results over
the past several years. This characteristic makes sampling and local grade
estimation very challenging and will be one of the objects of the current work
program.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As shown in the following linked longitudinal
and cross sections, the deposit is open on strike and at depth.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Tiriganiaq Longitudinal Section</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i008.jpg"></font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10<a name="PB_10_004804_7091"></a></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Infill
drilling at </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Tiriganiaq returned high
grade results from outside the current resource envelope in </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">shallow
depths.&#160; Examples of these intercepts are
</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">drill hole M-10-889 that yielded 24.9 g/t gold
over 7.8 metres, M-10-890A that yielded 7.9 g/t gold over 20.4 metres, as well
as M-10-875.&#160; These three holes show the
potential to extend the mineralization to the west and increase the size of the
planned Tiriganiaq open pit.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There were also high-grade intercepts at depth,
such as drill holes M-10-886, 904A, -907, -914 and drill hole M10-900, which
returned 7.0 g/t gold over 17 metres at about 570 metres below surface.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">11<a name="PB_11_004804_455"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='11',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Early Results from Nearby &#147;F&#148; Zone</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Early results from the F zone drilling suggest
that there is considerable potential outside the current resource
envelope.&#160; The F zone may have both open
pit and underground mining potential as well.&#160;
Drill holes M-10-910, -911, -912 and -913 returned high grades at
shallow depths, while holes M-10-901, -915 and -917 showed strong grade and
width as deep as 125 metres below surface.&#160;
The exploration program is still underway.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Meliadine F Zone Longitudinal Section</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Abitibi
Update &#151; Goldex and Lapa Begin Deep Underground Programs</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Deeper Drilling at Goldex Yields Intriguingly
Familiar Mineralization</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The objectives of the 2010 diamond drill
program at the Goldex mine were to convert the inferred resources to reserves
in the E zone (the eastern extremity of the GEZ zone, which is currently being
mined), to explore the eastern and western extensions of the GEZ zone as well
as at depth (the D zone), and to investigate the potential above the M zone.&#160; Through the end of July, 18,835 metres had
been drilled of the planned 28,206 metre Goldex program for 2010.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The E zone is undergoing conversion drilling on
a 30-metre grid pattern to determine if the current mine workings could extend
eastward.&#160; It is expected that 3,000
metres of underground diamond drilling will be done from the level 84
exploration drift before the end of 2010, as well as 4,000 metres from surface
to verify the gold potential above the E zone.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Three drill rigs are working to define and
extend resources in the deeper D zone.&#160;
This zone is located approximately 150 metres below the mine workings of
the GEZ zone, and was originally discovered in the mid-1990s.&#160; The most recent results are shown in the
table below, and the drill hole pierce points are shown on the Goldex
longitudinal section.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The long intercepts being returned, such as 161
metres of core length grading 2.0 g/t gold in drill hole 84-051, are
reminiscent of those from the GEZ zone above (1.6 million ounce gold
reserve).&#160; Because the geometry of D zone
is not yet fully defined, true widths could not be estimated.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Goldex Longitudinal Section</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">556.5</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.0%;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">*<i>Cannot determine true width yet, as the geometry of the D zone not yet
understood.</i></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">This
zone remains open in all directions and at depth.&#160; Further drilling is scheduled for 2010 and a
mining study is expected to be initiated in 2011.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:8.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Acquires
51% of Adventure Gold&#146;s Dubuisson Property Near Goldex</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In July&nbsp;2010,
the Company signed an agreement with Adventure Gold Inc. acquiring a 51%
interest in the 745 hectare Dubuisson property, immediately west of the Goldex
mine property.&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Dubuisson property straddles the Cadillac - Larder Lake fault and
includes a known gold deposit.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Dubuisson Property Location</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i012.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The gold system locally exceeds
20 metres in thickness and can be traced for more than 800 metres along
strike.&#160; This new property holds promise
for ore potential in close proximity to the Goldex property.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">14<a name="PB_14_124149_2897"></a></font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Lapa Underground Exploration Underway</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">There are two exploration programs underway at
the Lapa mine, using deep exploration drifts to expand and convert
mineralization to the east of the current mine workings.&#160; The two exploration drifts can be seen in the
Lapa longitudinal section and plan map.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Lapa Longitudinal Section</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i013.jpg"></font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">15<a name="PB_15_004804_3736"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='15',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Lapa Exploration Drifts</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i014.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A three-year, $2.8-million project commenced
earlier in 2010, driving a 970-metre-long tracked drift, approximately 1,010
metres below surface, to the east-southeast, following the southern contact of
the Cadillac - Larder Lake fault zone.&#160;
This fault zone is the major structural control for gold deposits in the
district.&#160; This drift will provide an
underground drill platform to test a favourable volcanic unit for
mineralization.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A smaller, recently approved, exploration
project involves driving a 385-metre-long trackless drift, approximately 980
metres below surface, to the east into the footwall beneath the Cadillac -
Larder Lake fault to convert an existing resource.&#160; The drift will allow for 9,400 metres of
conversion and exploration drilling, which should all be accomplished in 2011.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">16<a name="PB_16_124233_3020"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='16',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Regional Exploration</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Ellison Pilot Hole Intersects Westwood Zone</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Agnico-Eagle is conducting a deep drilling
program on its Ellison property, immediately west of the Company&#146;s LaRonde and
Bousquet properties, to determine if IAMGOLD Corporation&#146;s Westwood gold zone
crosses onto Ellison at depth.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Abitibi Regional Geology Map</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i015.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A 3,255-metre-long pilot drill hole was
completed in early July&nbsp;2010 at a vertical depth of 2,680 metres below
surface.&#160; Hole 114-10-16G, one of the
deepest drill holes ever drilled in Quebec, returned more than 70 metres of
mineralized core length (3,128 to 3,195 metres), confirming that both the
Westwood zone and a new zone are present on the Ellison property.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The first, a LaRonde-style mineralized
interval, returned 0.35 g/t gold and 0.34% copper over five metres.&#160; The second mineralized interval is believed
to represent the Westwood zone and returned 1.20 g/t gold over 10.5 metres,
including 2.90 g/t gold over 3.0 metres. There are plans for two branch holes
to be wedged out from the pilot hole to further investigate the mineralization.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">17<a name="PB_17_124247_7748"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='17',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Exploration Underway at Dieppe</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">North of Agnico-Eagle&#146;s Quebec mines, the
Company has initiated an exploration program on its 100%-owned Dieppe Township
property, located 145 kilometres north of Rouyn-Noranda, Quebec, and
immediately west of the operating Casa Berardi gold mine.&#160; The property covers more than ten kilometres
along the Casa Berardi Gold Trend.&#160; No
exploration work had taken place on the Dieppe Township property since the late
1980s, and a large portion of it had only been tested down to approximately 100
metres below surface.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Dieppe Township Property Location</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><img width="720" height="540" src="g171301ka01i016.jpg"></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">As part of the 2010 exploration program,
fifteen drill holes were completed to date on the Dieppe Township
property.&#160; Most of them intersected the
Casa Berardi Gold Trend and some have returned notable results.&#160; The most promising results were from drill
hole 157-10-10, which returned 2.90 g/t gold over 8.0 metres, including 5.10
g/t gold over 3.7 metres at a vertical depth of 150 metres.&#160; Underneath this interval, drill hole
157-10-13 returned 1.00 g/t gold over 10.5 metres including 1.90 g/t gold over
4.5 metres at about 220 metres</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">18<a name="PB_18_004804_563"></a></font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade color="#010101" align="left"></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='18',FILE='C:\JMS\105542\10-17130-1\task4267735\17130-1-ka-01.htm',USER='105542',CD='Sep 10 12:46 2010' -->



<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">vertical depth.&#160;
Closer to surface (30 metres vertical depth), another interval returned
26.80 g/t gold over 1.5 metres in a second structure with visible gold.&#160; The 2011 winter drilling program is expected
to follow up on these results.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">About Agnico-Eagle</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Agnico-Eagle is a long established
Canadian gold producer with operations located in Canada, Finland and Mexico
and exploration and development activities in Canada, Finland, Mexico and the
United States.&#160; Agnico-Eagle&#146;s LaRonde
mine is Canada&#146;s largest operating gold mine in terms of reserves.&#160; The Company has full exposure to higher gold
prices consistent with its policy of no forward gold sales.&#160; It has declared a cash dividend for 28
consecutive years.&#160; </font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Agnico-Eagle&#146;s registered office is located at 145 King Street East, Suite&nbsp;400,
Toronto, Ontario M5C 2Y7.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

disruptions, supply disruptions, damage to equipment, natural occurrences,

expansion at each of Agnico-Eagle&#146;s mines and growth projects proceeds on a

for gold, silver, zinc, copper and lead will be consistent with Agnico-Eagle&#146;s

the actual results to be materially different from those expressed or implied
by such forward-looking statements. Such risks include, but are not limited to:
the volatility of prices of gold and other metals; uncertainty of mineral
